29uint32 GetTargetFlagMask(SpellTargetObjectTypes objType)
30{
31 switch (objType)
32 {
33 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_DEST:
34 return TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION;
35 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT_AND_DEST:
36 return TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT;
37 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_CORPSE_ALLY:
38 return TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_ALLY;
39 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_CORPSE_ENEMY:
40 return TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_ENEMY;
41 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_CORPSE:
42 return TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_ALLY | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_ENEMY;
43 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT:
44 return TARGET_FLAG_UNIT;
45 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_GOBJ:
46 return TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT;
47 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_GOBJ_ITEM:
48 return TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM;
49 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_ITEM:
50 return TARGET_FLAG_ITEM;
51 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_SRC:
52 return TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION;
53 default:
54 return TARGET_FLAG_NONE;
55 }
56}

93float SpellImplicitTargetInfo::CalcDirectionAngle() const
94{
95 switch (GetDirectionType())
96 {
97 case TARGET_DIR_FRONT:
98 return 0.0f;
99 case TARGET_DIR_BACK:
100 return static_cast<float>(M_PI);
101 case TARGET_DIR_RIGHT:
102 return static_cast<float>(-M_PI / 2);
103 case TARGET_DIR_LEFT:
104 return static_cast<float>(M_PI / 2);
105 case TARGET_DIR_FRONT_RIGHT:
106 return static_cast<float>(-M_PI / 4);
107 case TARGET_DIR_BACK_RIGHT:
108 return static_cast<float>(-3 * M_PI / 4);
109 case TARGET_DIR_BACK_LEFT:
110 return static_cast<float>(3 * M_PI / 4);
111 case TARGET_DIR_FRONT_LEFT:
112 return static_cast<float>(M_PI / 4);
113 case TARGET_DIR_RANDOM:
114 return float(rand_norm()) * static_cast<float>(2 * M_PI);
115 default:
116 return 0.0f;
117 }
118}

125uint32 SpellImplicitTargetInfo::GetExplicitTargetMask(bool& srcSet, bool& dstSet) const
126{
127 uint32 targetMask = 0;
128 if (GetTarget() == TARGET_DEST_TRAJ)
129 {
130 if (!srcSet)
131 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION;
132 if (!dstSet)
133 targetMask |= TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION;
134 }
135 else
136 {
137 switch (GetReferenceType())
138 {
139 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_SRC:
140 if (srcSet)
141 break;
142 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION;
143 break;
144 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_DEST:
145 if (dstSet)
146 break;
147 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION;
148 break;
149 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_TARGET:
150 switch (GetObjectType())
151 {
152 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_GOBJ:
153 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT;
154 break;
155 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_GOBJ_ITEM:
156 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM;
157 break;
158 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT_AND_DEST:
159 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT:
160 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_DEST:
161 switch (GetCheckType())
162 {
163 case TARGET_CHECK_ENEMY:
164 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ENEMY;
165 break;
166 case TARGET_CHECK_ALLY:
167 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ALLY;
168 break;
169 case TARGET_CHECK_PARTY:
170 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PARTY;
171 break;
172 case TARGET_CHECK_RAID:
173 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_RAID;
174 break;
175 case TARGET_CHECK_PASSENGER:
176 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PASSENGER;
177 break;
178 case TARGET_CHECK_RAID_CLASS:
179 [[fallthrough]];
180 default:
181 targetMask = TARGET_FLAG_UNIT;
182 break;
183 }
184 break;
185 default:
186 break;
187 }
188 break;
189 default:
190 break;
191 }
192 }
193
194 switch (GetObjectType())
195 {
196 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_SRC:
197 srcSet = true;
198 break;
199 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_DEST:
200 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT_AND_DEST:
201 dstSet = true;
202 break;
203 default:
204 break;
205 }
206 return targetMask;
207}

324SpellEffectInfo::SpellEffectInfo(SpellEntry const* spellEntry, SpellInfo const* spellInfo, uint8 effIndex)
325{
326 _spellInfo = spellInfo;
327 _effIndex = effIndex;
328 Effect = spellEntry->Effect[effIndex];
329 ApplyAuraName = spellEntry->EffectApplyAuraName[effIndex];
330 Amplitude = spellEntry->EffectAmplitude[effIndex];
331 DieSides = spellEntry->EffectDieSides[effIndex];
332 RealPointsPerLevel = spellEntry->EffectRealPointsPerLevel[effIndex];
333 BasePoints = spellEntry->EffectBasePoints[effIndex];
334 PointsPerComboPoint = spellEntry->EffectPointsPerComboPoint[effIndex];
335 ValueMultiplier = spellEntry->EffectValueMultiplier[effIndex];
336 DamageMultiplier = spellEntry->EffectDamageMultiplier[effIndex];
337 BonusMultiplier = spellEntry->EffectBonusMultiplier[effIndex];
338 MiscValue = spellEntry->EffectMiscValue[effIndex];
339 MiscValueB = spellEntry->EffectMiscValueB[effIndex];
340 Mechanic = Mechanics(spellEntry->EffectMechanic[effIndex]);
341 TargetA = SpellImplicitTargetInfo(spellEntry->EffectImplicitTargetA[effIndex]);
342 TargetB = SpellImplicitTargetInfo(spellEntry->EffectImplicitTargetB[effIndex]);
343 RadiusEntry = spellEntry->EffectRadiusIndex[effIndex] ? sSpellRadiusStore.LookupEntry(spellEntry->EffectRadiusIndex[effIndex]) : nullptr;
344 ChainTarget = spellEntry->EffectChainTarget[effIndex];
345 ItemType = spellEntry->EffectItemType[effIndex];
346 TriggerSpell = spellEntry->EffectTriggerSpell[effIndex];
347 SpellClassMask = spellEntry->EffectSpellClassMask[effIndex];
348 ImplicitTargetConditions = nullptr;
349}

382 Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AREA_AURA_PET ||

406
407int32 SpellEffectInfo::CalcValue(Unit const* caster, int32 const* bp, Unit const* /*target*/) const
408{
409 float basePointsPerLevel = RealPointsPerLevel;
410 int32 basePoints = bp ? *bp : BasePoints;
411 int32 randomPoints = int32(DieSides);
412
413 // base amount modification based on spell lvl vs caster lvl
414 // xinef: added basePointsPerLevel check
415 if (caster && basePointsPerLevel != 0.0f)
416 {
417 int32 level = int32(caster->getLevel());
418 if (level > int32(_spellInfo->MaxLevel) && _spellInfo->MaxLevel > 0)
419 level = int32(_spellInfo->MaxLevel);
420 else if (level < int32(_spellInfo->BaseLevel))
421 level = int32(_spellInfo->BaseLevel);
422
423 // xinef: if base level is greater than spell level, reduce by base level (eg. pilgrims foods)
424 level -= int32(std::max(_spellInfo->BaseLevel, _spellInfo->SpellLevel));
425 basePoints += int32(level * basePointsPerLevel);
426 }
427
428 // roll in a range <1;EffectDieSides> as of patch 3.3.3
429 switch (randomPoints)
430 {
431 case 0:
432 break;
433 case 1:
434 basePoints += 1;
435 break; // range 1..1
436 default:
437 // range can have positive (1..rand) and negative (rand..1) values, so order its for irand
438 int32 randvalue = (randomPoints >= 1)
439 ? irand(1, randomPoints)
440 : irand(randomPoints, 1);
441
442 basePoints += randvalue;
443 break;
444 }
445
446 float value = float(basePoints);
447
448 // random damage
449 if (caster)
450 {
451 // bonus amount from combo points
452 if (uint8 comboPoints = caster->GetComboPoints())
453 {
454 value += PointsPerComboPoint * comboPoints;
455 }
456
457 value = caster->ApplyEffectModifiers(_spellInfo, _effIndex, value);
458
459 // amount multiplication based on caster's level
460 if (!caster->IsControlledByPlayer() &&
461 _spellInfo->SpellLevel && _spellInfo->SpellLevel != caster->getLevel() &&
462 !basePointsPerLevel && _spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_SCALES_WITH_CREATURE_LEVEL))
463 {
464 bool canEffectScale = false;
465 switch (Effect)
466 {
467 case SPELL_EFFECT_SCHOOL_DAMAGE:
468 case SPELL_EFFECT_DUMMY:
469 case SPELL_EFFECT_POWER_DRAIN:
470 case SPELL_EFFECT_HEALTH_LEECH:
471 case SPELL_EFFECT_HEAL:
472 case SPELL_EFFECT_WEAPON_DAMAGE:
473 case SPELL_EFFECT_POWER_BURN:
474 case SPELL_EFFECT_SCRIPT_EFFECT:
475 case SPELL_EFFECT_NORMALIZED_WEAPON_DMG:
476 case SPELL_EFFECT_FORCE_CAST_WITH_VALUE:
477 case SPELL_EFFECT_TRIGGER_SPELL_WITH_VALUE:
478 case SPELL_EFFECT_TRIGGER_MISSILE_SPELL_WITH_VALUE:
479 canEffectScale = true;
480 break;
481 default:
482 break;
483 }
484
485 switch (ApplyAuraName)
486 {
487 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE:
488 case SPELL_AURA_DUMMY:
489 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HEAL:
490 case SPELL_AURA_DAMAGE_SHIELD:
491 case SPELL_AURA_PROC_TRIGGER_DAMAGE:
492 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_LEECH:
493 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_MANA_LEECH:
494 case SPELL_AURA_SCHOOL_ABSORB:
495 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL_WITH_VALUE:
496 canEffectScale = true;
497 break;
498 default:
499 break;
500 }
501
502 if (canEffectScale)
503 {
504 GtNPCManaCostScalerEntry const* spellScaler = sGtNPCManaCostScalerStore.LookupEntry(_spellInfo->SpellLevel - 1);
505 GtNPCManaCostScalerEntry const* casterScaler = sGtNPCManaCostScalerStore.LookupEntry(caster->getLevel() - 1);
506 if (spellScaler && casterScaler)
507 value *= casterScaler->ratio / spellScaler->ratio;
508 }
509 }
510 }
511
512 return int32(value);
513}
514
515int32 SpellEffectInfo::CalcBaseValue(int32 value) const
516{
517 if (DieSides == 0)
518 return value;
519 else
520 return value - 1;
521}
522
523float SpellEffectInfo::CalcValueMultiplier(Unit* caster, Spell* spell) const
524{
525 float multiplier = ValueMultiplier;
526 if (Player* modOwner = (caster ? caster->GetSpellModOwner() : nullptr))
527 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_VALUE_MULTIPLIER, multiplier, spell);
528 return multiplier;
529}
530
531float SpellEffectInfo::CalcDamageMultiplier(Unit* caster, Spell* spell) const
532{
533 float multiplier = DamageMultiplier;
534 if (Player* modOwner = (caster ? caster->GetSpellModOwner() : nullptr))
535 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_DAMAGE_MULTIPLIER, multiplier, spell);
536 return multiplier;
537}
538
539bool SpellEffectInfo::HasRadius() const
540{
541 return RadiusEntry != nullptr;
542}
543
544float SpellEffectInfo::CalcRadius(Unit* caster, Spell* spell) const
545{
546 if (!HasRadius())
547 return 0.0f;
548
549 float radius = RadiusEntry->RadiusMin;
550 if (caster)
551 {
552 radius += RadiusEntry->RadiusPerLevel * caster->getLevel();
553 radius = std::min(radius, RadiusEntry->RadiusMax);
554 if (Player* modOwner = caster->GetSpellModOwner())
555 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_RADIUS, radius, spell);
556 }
557
558 return radius;
559}

561uint32 SpellEffectInfo::GetProvidedTargetMask() const
562{
563 return GetTargetFlagMask(TargetA.GetObjectType()) | GetTargetFlagMask(TargetB.GetObjectType());
564}
565
566uint32 SpellEffectInfo::GetMissingTargetMask(bool srcSet /*= false*/, bool dstSet /*= false*/, uint32 mask /*=0*/) const
567{
568 uint32 effImplicitTargetMask = GetTargetFlagMask(GetUsedTargetObjectType());
569 uint32 providedTargetMask = GetTargetFlagMask(TargetA.GetObjectType()) | GetTargetFlagMask(TargetB.GetObjectType()) | mask;
570
571 // remove all flags covered by effect target mask
572 if (providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK)
573 effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK);
574 if (providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK)
575 effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK);
576 if (providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM)
577 effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT | TARGET_FLAG_ITEM);
578 if (providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT)
579 effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM);
580 if (providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_ITEM)
581 effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_ITEM | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM);
582 if (dstSet || providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION)
583 effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION);
584 if (srcSet || providedTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION)
585 effImplicitTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION);
586
587 return effImplicitTargetMask;
588}

970
971bool SpellInfo::IsAbilityLearnedWithProfession() const
972{
973 SkillLineAbilityMapBounds bounds = sSpellMgr->GetSkillLineAbilityMapBounds(Id);
974
975 for (SkillLineAbilityMap::const_iterator _spell_idx = bounds.first; _spell_idx != bounds.second; ++_spell_idx)
976 {
977 SkillLineAbilityEntry const* pAbility = _spell_idx->second;
978 if (!pAbility || pAbility->AcquireMethod != SKILL_LINE_ABILITY_LEARNED_ON_SKILL_VALUE)
979 continue;
980
981 if (pAbility->MinSkillLineRank > 0)
982 return true;
983 }
984
985 return false;
986}
987
988bool SpellInfo::IsAbilityOfSkillType(uint32 skillType) const
989{
990 SkillLineAbilityMapBounds bounds = sSpellMgr->GetSkillLineAbilityMapBounds(Id);
991
992 for (SkillLineAbilityMap::const_iterator _spell_idx = bounds.first; _spell_idx != bounds.second; ++_spell_idx)
993 if (_spell_idx->second->SkillLine == uint32(skillType))
994 return true;
995
996 return false;
997}

1020
1021bool SpellInfo::NeedsToBeTriggeredByCaster(SpellInfo const* triggeringSpell, uint8 effIndex) const
1022{
1023 if (NeedsExplicitUnitTarget())
1024 return true;
1025
1026 // pussywizard:
1027 if (effIndex < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS && (triggeringSpell->Effects[effIndex].TargetA.GetCheckType() == TARGET_CHECK_ENTRY || triggeringSpell->Effects[effIndex].TargetB.GetCheckType() == TARGET_CHECK_ENTRY))
1028 {
1029 // xinef:
1030 if (Id == 60563)
1031 return true;
1032
1033 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
1034 if (Effects[i].IsEffect() && (Effects[i].TargetA.GetCheckType() == TARGET_CHECK_ENTRY || Effects[i].TargetB.GetCheckType() == TARGET_CHECK_ENTRY))
1035 return true;
1036 }
1037
1038 /*
1039 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
1040 {
1041 if (Effects[i].IsEffect())
1042 {
1043 if (Effects[i].TargetA.GetSelectionCategory() == TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_CHANNEL
1044 || Effects[i].TargetB.GetSelectionCategory() == TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_CHANNEL)
1045 return true;
1046 }
1047 }
1048 */
1049
1050 if (triggeringSpell->IsChanneled())
1051 {
1052 uint32 mask = 0;
1053 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
1054 {
1055 if (Effects[i].TargetA.GetTarget() != TARGET_UNIT_CASTER && Effects[i].TargetA.GetTarget() != TARGET_DEST_CASTER)
1056 mask |= Effects[i].GetProvidedTargetMask();
1057 }
1058
1059 if (mask & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK)
1060 return true;
1061 }
1062
1063 return false;
1064}

1086bool SpellInfo::IsAutocastable() const
1087{
1088 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_PASSIVE))
1089 return false;
1090 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR1_NO_AUTOCAST_AI))
1091 return false;
1092 return true;

1095bool SpellInfo::ComputeIsStackableWithRanks() const
1096{
1097 if (IsPassive())
1098 return false;
1099 if (PowerType != POWER_MANA && PowerType != POWER_HEALTH)
1100 return false;
1101 if (IsProfessionOrRiding())
1102 return false;
1103
1104 if (IsAbilityLearnedWithProfession())
1105 return false;
1106
1107 // All stance spells. if any better way, change it.
1108 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
1109 {
1110 switch (SpellFamilyName)
1111 {
1112 case SPELLFAMILY_PALADIN:
1113 // Paladin aura Spell
1114 if (Effects[i].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AREA_AURA_RAID)
1115 return false;
1116 break;
1117 case SPELLFAMILY_DRUID:
1118 // Druid form Spell
1119 if (Effects[i].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA &&
1120 Effects[i].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_SHAPESHIFT)
1121 return false;
1122 break;
1123 }
1124 }
1125 return true;
1126}

1276bool SpellInfo::IsAffectedBySpellMod(SpellModifier const* mod) const
1277{
1278 // xinef: dont check duration mod
1279 if (mod->op != SPELLMOD_DURATION)
1280 if (!IsAffectedBySpellMods())
1281 return false;
1282
1283 SpellInfo const* affectSpell = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(mod->spellId);
1284
1285 if (!affectSpell)
1286 {
1287 return false;
1288 }
1289
1290 if (!sScriptMgr->OnIsAffectedBySpellModCheck(affectSpell, this, mod))
1291 {
1292 return true;
1293 }
1294
1295 // False if affect_spell == nullptr or spellFamily not equal
1296 if (affectSpell->SpellFamilyName != SpellFamilyName)
1297 return false;
1298
1299 // true
1300 if (mod->mask & SpellFamilyFlags)
1301 return true;
1302
1303 return false;

1307{

1312 }
1313

1315 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_NO_IMMUNITIES))

1322 aura->Mechanic != MECHANIC_INVULNERABILITY &&
1323 aura->Mechanic != MECHANIC_BANISH)
1324 {
1325 return true;

1327
1328 }

1333bool SpellInfo::CanDispelAura(SpellInfo const* aura) const
1334{
1335 // Xinef: Passive auras cannot be dispelled
1336 if (aura->IsPassive())
1337 return false;
1338
1339 // These auras (like Divine Shield) can't be dispelled
1340 if (aura->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_NO_IMMUNITIES))
1341 return false;
1342
1343 // These spells (like Mass Dispel) can dispell all auras
1344 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_NO_IMMUNITIES))
1345 return true;
1346
1347 // These auras (Cyclone for example) are not dispelable
1348 if ((aura->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR1_IMMUNITY_TO_HOSTILE_AND_FRIENDLY_EFFECTS) && aura->Mechanic != MECHANIC_NONE)
1349 || aura->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR2_NO_SCHOOL_IMMUNITIES))
1350 {
1351 return false;
1352 }
1353
1354 return true;

1417SpellCastResult SpellInfo::CheckShapeshift(uint32 form) const
1418{
1419 // talents that learn spells can have stance requirements that need ignore
1420 // (this requirement only for client-side stance show in talent description)
1421 if (GetTalentSpellCost(Id) > 0 &&
1422 (Effects[0].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_LEARN_SPELL || Effects[1].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_LEARN_SPELL || Effects[2].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_LEARN_SPELL))
1423 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1424
1425 uint32 stanceMask = (form ? 1 << (form - 1) : 0);
1426
1427 if (stanceMask & StancesNot) // can explicitly not be casted in this stance
1428 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_SHAPESHIFT;
1429
1430 if (stanceMask & Stances) // can explicitly be casted in this stance
1431 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1432
1433 bool actAsShifted = false;
1434 SpellShapeshiftEntry const* shapeInfo = nullptr;
1435 if (form > 0)
1436 {
1437 shapeInfo = sSpellShapeshiftStore.LookupEntry(form);
1438 if (!shapeInfo)
1439 {
1440 LOG_ERROR("spells", "GetErrorAtShapeshiftedCast: unknown shapeshift {}", form);
1441 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1442 }
1443 actAsShifted = !(shapeInfo->flags1 & 1); // shapeshift acts as normal form for spells
1444 }
1445
1446 if (actAsShifted)
1447 {
1448 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_NOT_SHAPESHIFTED)) // not while shapeshifted
1449 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_SHAPESHIFT;
1450 else if (Stances != 0) // needs other shapeshift
1451 return SPELL_FAILED_ONLY_SHAPESHIFT;
1452 }
1453 else
1454 {
1455 // needs shapeshift
1456 if (!(AttributesEx2 & SPELL_ATTR2_ALLOW_WHILE_NOT_SHAPESHIFTED) && Stances != 0)
1457 return SPELL_FAILED_ONLY_SHAPESHIFT;
1458 }
1459
1460 // Check if stance disables cast of not-stance spells
1461 // Example: cannot cast any other spells in zombie or ghoul form
1462 // TODO: Find a way to disable use of these spells clientside
1463 if (shapeInfo && shapeInfo->flags1 & 0x400)
1464 {
1465 if (!(stanceMask & Stances))
1466 return SPELL_FAILED_ONLY_SHAPESHIFT;
1467 }
1468
1469 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1470}
1471
1472SpellCastResult SpellInfo::CheckLocation(uint32 map_id, uint32 zone_id, uint32 area_id, Player const* player /*= nullptr*/, bool strict /*= true*/) const
1473{
1474 // normal case
1475 if (AreaGroupId > 0)
1476 {
1477 bool found = false;
1478 AreaGroupEntry const* groupEntry = sAreaGroupStore.LookupEntry(AreaGroupId);
1479 while (groupEntry)
1480 {
1481 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_GROUP_AREA_IDS; ++i)
1482 if (groupEntry->AreaId[i] == zone_id || groupEntry->AreaId[i] == area_id)
1483 found = true;
1484 if (found || !groupEntry->nextGroup)
1485 break;
1486 // Try search in next group
1487 groupEntry = sAreaGroupStore.LookupEntry(groupEntry->nextGroup);
1488 }
1489
1490 if (!found)
1491 return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1492 }
1493
1494 // continent limitation (virtual continent)
1495 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR4_ONLY_FLYING_AREAS) && (area_id || zone_id))
1496 {
1497 AreaTableEntry const* areaEntry = sAreaTableStore.LookupEntry(area_id);
1498 if (!areaEntry)
1499 {
1500 areaEntry = sAreaTableStore.LookupEntry(zone_id);
1501 }
1502
1503 if (!areaEntry || !areaEntry->IsFlyable() || (strict && (areaEntry->flags & AREA_FLAG_NO_FLY_ZONE) != 0) || !player->canFlyInZone(map_id, zone_id, this))
1504 {
1505 return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1506 }
1507 }
1508
1509 // raid instance limitation
1510 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR6_NOT_IN_RAID_INSTANCES))
1511 {
1512 MapEntry const* mapEntry = sMapStore.LookupEntry(map_id);
1513 if (!mapEntry || mapEntry->IsRaid())
1514 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_IN_RAID_INSTANCE;
1515 }
1516
1517 // DB base check (if non empty then must fit at least single for allow)
1518 SpellAreaMapBounds saBounds = sSpellMgr->GetSpellAreaMapBounds(Id);
1519 if (saBounds.first != saBounds.second)
1520 {
1521 for (SpellAreaMap::const_iterator itr = saBounds.first; itr != saBounds.second; ++itr)
1522 {
1523 if (itr->second.IsFitToRequirements(player, zone_id, area_id))
1524 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1525 }
1526 return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1527 }
1528
1529 // bg spell checks
1530 switch (Id)
1531 {
1532 case 23333: // Warsong Flag
1533 case 23335: // Silverwing Flag
1534 return map_id == 489 && player && player->InBattleground() ? SPELL_CAST_OK : SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1535 case 34976: // Netherstorm Flag
1536 return map_id == 566 && player && player->InBattleground() ? SPELL_CAST_OK : SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1537 case 2584: // Waiting to Resurrect
1538 case 22011: // Spirit Heal Channel
1539 case 22012: // Spirit Heal
1540 case 24171: // Resurrection Impact Visual
1541 case 42792: // Recently Dropped Flag
1542 case 43681: // Inactive
1543 case 44535: // Spirit Heal (mana)
1544 {
1545 MapEntry const* mapEntry = sMapStore.LookupEntry(map_id);
1546 if (!mapEntry)
1547 return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1548
1549 return zone_id == 4197 || (mapEntry->IsBattleground() && player && player->InBattleground()) ? SPELL_CAST_OK : SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1550 }
1551 case 32724: // Gold Team (Alliance)
1552 case 32725: // Green Team (Alliance)
1553 case 35774: // Gold Team (Horde)
1554 case 35775: // Green Team (Horde)
1555 {
1556 MapEntry const* mapEntry = sMapStore.LookupEntry(map_id);
1557 if (!mapEntry)
1558 return SPELL_FAILED_INCORRECT_AREA;
1559
1560 return mapEntry->IsBattleArena() && player && player->InBattleground() ? SPELL_CAST_OK : SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA;
1561 }
1562 }
1563
1564 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1565}
1566
1567bool SpellInfo::IsStrongerAuraActive(Unit const* caster, Unit const* target) const
1568{
1569 if (!target)
1570 return false;
1571
1572 // xinef: check spell group
1573 uint32 groupId = sSpellMgr->GetSpellGroup(Id);
1574 if (!groupId)
1575 return false;
1576
1577 SpellGroupSpecialFlags sFlag = sSpellMgr->GetSpellGroupSpecialFlags(Id);
1578 if (sFlag & SPELL_GROUP_SPECIAL_FLAG_SKIP_STRONGER_CHECK)
1579 return false;
1580
1581 for (uint8 i = EFFECT_0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
1582 {
1583 // xinef: Skip Empty effects
1584 if (!Effects[i].IsEffect())
1585 continue;
1586
1587 // xinef: if non-aura effect is preset - return false
1588 if (!Effects[i].IsAura())
1589 return false;
1590
1591 // xinef: aura is periodic - return false
1592 if (Effects[i].Amplitude)
1593 return false;
1594
1595 // xinef: exclude dummy auras
1596 if (Effects[i].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_DUMMY)
1597 return false;
1598 }
1599
1600 for (uint8 i = EFFECT_0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
1601 {
1602 // xinef: skip non-aura efects
1603 if (!Effects[i].IsAura())
1604 return false;
1605
1606 Unit::AuraEffectList const& auraList = target->GetAuraEffectsByType((AuraType)Effects[i].ApplyAuraName);
1607 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator iter = auraList.begin(); iter != auraList.end(); ++iter)
1608 {
1609 // xinef: aura is not groupped or in different group
1610 uint32 auraGroup = (*iter)->GetAuraGroup();
1611 if (!auraGroup || auraGroup != groupId)
1612 continue;
1613
1614 if (IsRankOf((*iter)->GetSpellInfo()) && (sFlag & SPELL_GROUP_SPECIAL_FLAG_SKIP_STRONGER_SAME_SPELL))
1615 {
1616 continue;
1617 }
1618
1619 // xinef: check priority before effect mask
1620 if (sFlag >= SPELL_GROUP_SPECIAL_FLAG_PRIORITY1 && sFlag <= SPELL_GROUP_SPECIAL_FLAG_PRIORITY4)
1621 {
1622 SpellGroupSpecialFlags sFlagCurr = sSpellMgr->GetSpellGroupSpecialFlags((*iter)->GetId());
1623 if (sFlagCurr >= SPELL_GROUP_SPECIAL_FLAG_PRIORITY1 && sFlagCurr <= SPELL_GROUP_SPECIAL_FLAG_PRIORITY4 && sFlagCurr < sFlag)
1624 {
1625 return true;
1626 }
1627 }
1628
1629 // xinef: check aura effect equal auras only, some auras have different effects on different ranks - check rank also
1630 if (!IsAuraEffectEqual((*iter)->GetSpellInfo()) && !IsRankOf((*iter)->GetSpellInfo()))
1631 continue;
1632
1633 // xinef: misc value mismatches
1634 // xinef: commented, checked above
1635 //if (Effects[i].MiscValue != (*iter)->GetMiscValue())
1636 // continue;
1637
1638 // xinef: should not happen, or effect is not active - stronger one is present
1639 AuraApplication* aurApp = (*iter)->GetBase()->GetApplicationOfTarget(target->GetGUID());
1640 if (!aurApp || !aurApp->IsActive((*iter)->GetEffIndex()))
1641 continue;
1642
1643 // xinef: assume that all spells are either positive or negative, otherwise they should not be in one group
1644 // xinef: take custom values into account
1645
1646 int32 basePoints = Effects[i].BasePoints;
1647 int32 duration = GetMaxDuration();
1648
1649 // xinef: should have the same id, can be different if spell is triggered
1650 // xinef: have to fix spell mods for triggered spell, turn off current spellmodtakingspell for preparing and restore after
1651 if (Player const* player = caster->GetSpellModOwner())
1652 if (player->m_spellModTakingSpell && player->m_spellModTakingSpell->m_spellInfo->Id == Id)
1653 basePoints = player->m_spellModTakingSpell->GetSpellValue()->EffectBasePoints[i];
1654
1655 int32 curValue = std::abs(Effects[i].CalcValue(caster, &basePoints));
1656 int32 auraValue = (sFlag & SPELL_GROUP_SPECIAL_FLAG_BASE_AMOUNT_CHECK) ?
1657 std::abs((*iter)->GetSpellInfo()->Effects[(*iter)->GetEffIndex()].CalcValue((*iter)->GetCaster())) :
1658 std::abs((*iter)->GetAmount());
1659
1660 // xinef: for same spells, divide amount by stack amount
1661 if (Id == (*iter)->GetId())
1662 auraValue /= (*iter)->GetBase()->GetStackAmount();
1663
1664 if (curValue < auraValue)
1665 return true;
1666
1667 // xinef: little hack, if current spell is the same as aura spell, asume it is not stronger
1668 // xinef: if values are the same, duration mods should be taken into account but they are almost always passive
1669 if (curValue == auraValue)
1670 {
1671 if (Id == (*iter)->GetId())
1672 continue;
1673 if (!(*iter)->GetBase()->IsPassive() && duration < (*iter)->GetBase()->GetDuration())
1674 return true;
1675 }
1676 }
1677 }
1678
1679 return false;
1680}
1681
1682bool SpellInfo::IsAuraEffectEqual(SpellInfo const* otherSpellInfo) const
1683{
1684 uint8 matchCount = 0;
1685 uint8 auraCount = 0;
1686 for (uint8 i = EFFECT_0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
1687 {
1688 // xinef: skip non-aura efects
1689 if (!Effects[i].IsAura())
1690 continue;
1691
1692 bool effectFound = false;
1693 for (uint8 j = EFFECT_0; j < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++j)
1694 {
1695 if (!otherSpellInfo->Effects[j].IsAura())
1696 continue;
1697
1698 if (Effects[i].ApplyAuraName != otherSpellInfo->Effects[j].ApplyAuraName || Effects[i].MiscValue != otherSpellInfo->Effects[j].MiscValue)
1699 continue;
1700
1701 effectFound = true;
1702 break;
1703 }
1704
1705 if (!effectFound)
1706 return false;
1707 ++matchCount;
1708 }
1709
1710 for (uint8 i = EFFECT_0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
1711 {
1712 if (Effects[i].IsAura())
1713 ++auraCount;
1714 if (otherSpellInfo->Effects[i].IsAura())
1715 ++auraCount;
1716 }
1717
1718 return matchCount * 2 == auraCount;
1719}
1720
1721bool SpellInfo::ValidateAttribute6SpellDamageMods(Unit const* caster, const AuraEffect* auraEffect, bool isDot) const
1722{
1723 // Xinef: no attribute
1724 if (!(AttributesEx6 & SPELL_ATTR6_IGNORE_CASTER_DAMAGE_MODIFIERS))
1725 return true;
1726
1727 // Xinef we have a hook to decide which auras should profit to the spell, by default no profits
1728 // Xinef: Scourge Strike - Trigger
1729 if (Id == 70890 && auraEffect)
1730 {
1731 SpellInfo const* auraInfo = auraEffect->GetSpellInfo();
1732 return auraInfo->SpellIconID == 3086 ||
1733 (auraInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_DEATHKNIGHT && (auraInfo->SpellFamilyFlags & flag96(8388608, 64, 16) || auraInfo->SpellIconID == 235 || auraInfo->SpellIconID == 154));
1734 }
1735 // Xinef: Necrosis, no profits for done and taken
1736 else if (Id == 51460)
1737 return false;
1738
1739 // Xinef: Do not affect dots and auras obtained from items, only affected by self casted auras
1740 return !isDot && auraEffect && (auraEffect->GetAmount() < 0 || (auraEffect->GetCasterGUID() == caster->GetGUID() && auraEffect->GetSpellInfo()->SpellFamilyName == SpellFamilyName)) && !auraEffect->GetBase()->GetCastItemGUID();
1741}
1742
1743SpellCastResult SpellInfo::CheckTarget(Unit const* caster, WorldObject const* target, bool implicit) const
1744{
1745 if (AttributesEx & SPELL_ATTR1_EXCLUDE_CASTER && caster == target)
1746 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1747
1748 // check visibility - ignore stealth for implicit (area) targets
1749 if (!(AttributesEx6 & SPELL_ATTR6_IGNORE_PHASE_SHIFT) && !caster->CanSeeOrDetect(target, implicit))
1750 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1751
1752 Unit const* unitTarget = target->ToUnit();
1753
1754 // creature/player specific target checks
1755 if (unitTarget)
1756 {
1757 // xinef: spells cannot be cast if player is in fake combat also
1758 if (AttributesEx & SPELL_ATTR1_ONLY_PEACEFUL_TARGETS && (unitTarget->IsInCombat() || unitTarget->IsPetInCombat()))
1759 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_AFFECTING_COMBAT;
1760
1761 // only spells with SPELL_ATTR3_ONLY_ON_GHOSTS can target ghosts
1762 if (((IsRequiringDeadTarget() != 0) != unitTarget->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_GHOST)) && !(IsDeathPersistent() && IsAllowingDeadTarget()))
1763 {
1764 if (AttributesEx3 & SPELL_ATTR3_ONLY_ON_GHOSTS)
1765 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_NOT_GHOST;
1766 else
1767 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1768 }
1769
1770 if (caster != unitTarget)
1771 {
1772 if (caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1773 {
1774 // Do not allow these spells to target creatures not tapped by us (Banish, Polymorph, many quest spells)
1775 if (AttributesEx2 & SPELL_ATTR2_CANNOT_CAST_ON_TAPPED)
1776 if (Creature const* targetCreature = unitTarget->ToCreature())
1777 if (targetCreature->hasLootRecipient() && !targetCreature->isTappedBy(caster->ToPlayer()))
1778 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_CAST_ON_TAPPED;
1779
1780 if (AttributesCu & SPELL_ATTR0_CU_PICKPOCKET)
1781 {
1782 if (unitTarget->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1783 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1784 else if ((unitTarget->GetCreatureTypeMask() & CREATURE_TYPEMASK_HUMANOID_OR_UNDEAD) == 0)
1785 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_NO_POCKETS;
1786 }
1787
1788 // Not allow disarm unarmed player
1789 if (Mechanic == MECHANIC_DISARM)
1790 {
1791 bool valid = false;
1792 for (uint8 i = BASE_ATTACK; i < MAX_ATTACK; ++i)
1793 {
1794 AuraType disarmAuraType = SPELL_AURA_MOD_DISARM;
1795 switch (i)
1796 {
1797 case OFF_ATTACK:
1798 disarmAuraType = SPELL_AURA_MOD_DISARM_OFFHAND;
1799 break;
1800 case RANGED_ATTACK:
1801 disarmAuraType = SPELL_AURA_MOD_DISARM_RANGED;
1802 break;
1803 }
1804
1805 if (HasAura(disarmAuraType))
1806 {
1807 if (Player const* player = unitTarget->ToPlayer())
1808 {
1809 if (player->GetWeaponForAttack(WeaponAttackType(BASE_ATTACK + i), true))
1810 {
1811 valid = true;
1812 break;
1813 }
1814 }
1815 else if (unitTarget->GetUInt32Value(UNIT_VIRTUAL_ITEM_SLOT_ID + i))
1816 {
1817 valid = true;
1818 break;
1819 }
1820 }
1821 }
1822
1823 if (!valid)
1824 {
1825 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_NO_WEAPONS;
1826 }
1827 }
1828 }
1829 }
1830 }
1831 // corpse specific target checks
1832 else if (Corpse const* corpseTarget = target->ToCorpse())
1833 {
1834 // cannot target bare bones
1835 if (corpseTarget->GetType() == CORPSE_BONES)
1836 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1837 // we have to use owner for some checks (aura preventing resurrection for example)
1838 if (Player* owner = ObjectAccessor::FindPlayer(corpseTarget->GetOwnerGUID()))
1839 unitTarget = owner;
1840 // we're not interested in corpses without owner
1841 else
1842 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1843 }
1844 // other types of objects - always valid
1845 else return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1846
1847 // corpseOwner and unit specific target checks
1848 if (AttributesEx3 & SPELL_ATTR3_ONLY_ON_PLAYER && !unitTarget->ToPlayer())
1849 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_NOT_PLAYER;
1850
1851 if (!IsAllowingDeadTarget() && !unitTarget->IsAlive())
1852 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGETS_DEAD;
1853
1854 // check this flag only for implicit targets (chain and area), allow to explicitly target units for spells like Shield of Righteousness
1855 if (implicit && AttributesEx6 & SPELL_ATTR6_DO_NOT_CHAIN_TO_CROWD_CONTROLLED_TARGETS && !unitTarget->CanFreeMove())
1856 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1857
1858 // checked in Unit::IsValidAttack/AssistTarget, shouldn't be checked for ENTRY targets
1859 //if (!(AttributesEx6 & SPELL_ATTR6_CAN_TARGET_UNTARGETABLE) && target->HasUnitFlag(UNIT_FLAG_NOT_SELECTABLE))
1860 // return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1861
1862 //if (!(AttributesEx6 & SPELL_ATTR6_NO_AURA_LOG)
1863
1864 if (!CheckTargetCreatureType(unitTarget))
1865 {
1866 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1867 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_IS_PLAYER;
1868 else
1869 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1870 }
1871
1872 // check GM mode and GM invisibility - only for player casts (npc casts are controlled by AI) and negative spells
1873 if (unitTarget != caster && (caster->IsControlledByPlayer() || !IsPositive()) && unitTarget->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
1874 {
1875 if (!unitTarget->ToPlayer()->IsVisible())
1876 return SPELL_FAILED_BM_OR_INVISGOD;
1877
1878 if (unitTarget->ToPlayer()->IsGameMaster())
1879 return SPELL_FAILED_BM_OR_INVISGOD;
1880 }
1881
1882 // not allow casting on flying player
1883 if (unitTarget->IsInFlight() && !HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_CU_ALLOW_INFLIGHT_TARGET))
1884 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1885
1886 /* TARGET_UNIT_MASTER gets blocked here for passengers, because the whole idea of this check is to
1887 not allow passengers to be implicitly hit by spells, however this target type should be an exception,
1888 if this is left it kills spells that award kill credit from vehicle to master (few spells),
1889 the use of these 2 covers passenger target check, logically, if vehicle cast this to master it should always hit
1890 him, because it would be it's passenger, there's no such case where this gets to fail legitimacy, this problem
1891 cannot be solved from within the check in other way since target type cannot be called for the spell currently
1892 Spell examples: [ID - 52864 Devour Water, ID - 52862 Devour Wind, ID - 49370 Wyrmrest Defender: Destabilize Azure Dragonshrine Effect] */
1893 if (!caster->IsVehicle() && caster->GetCharmerOrOwner() != target)
1894 {
1895 if (TargetAuraState && !unitTarget->HasAuraState(AuraStateType(TargetAuraState), this, caster))
1896 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_AURASTATE;
1897
1898 if (TargetAuraStateNot && unitTarget->HasAuraState(AuraStateType(TargetAuraStateNot), this, caster))
1899 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_AURASTATE;
1900 }
1901
1902 if (TargetAuraSpell && !unitTarget->HasAura(sSpellMgr->GetSpellIdForDifficulty(TargetAuraSpell, caster)))
1903 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_AURASTATE;
1904
1905 if (ExcludeTargetAuraSpell && unitTarget->HasAura(sSpellMgr->GetSpellIdForDifficulty(ExcludeTargetAuraSpell, caster)))
1906 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_AURASTATE;
1907
1908 if (unitTarget->HasAuraType(SPELL_AURA_PREVENT_RESURRECTION) && !HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR7_BYPASS_NO_RESURRECTION_AURA))
1909 if (HasEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_SELF_RESURRECT) || HasEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_RESURRECT) || HasEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_RESURRECT_NEW))
1910 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_CANNOT_BE_RESURRECTED;
1911
1912 // xinef: check if stronger aura is active
1913 if (IsStrongerAuraActive(caster, unitTarget))
1914 return SPELL_FAILED_AURA_BOUNCED;
1915
1916 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1917}
1918
1919SpellCastResult SpellInfo::CheckExplicitTarget(Unit const* caster, WorldObject const* target, Item const* itemTarget) const
1920{
1921 uint32 neededTargets = GetExplicitTargetMask();
1922 if (!target)
1923 {
1924 if (neededTargets & (TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK))
1925 if (!(neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM) || !itemTarget)
1926 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1927 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1928 }
1929
1930 if (Unit const* unitTarget = target->ToUnit())
1931 {
1932 if (neededTargets & (TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ENEMY | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ALLY | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_RAID | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PARTY | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MINIPET | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PASSENGER))
1933 {
1934 if (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ENEMY)
1935 if (caster->_IsValidAttackTarget(unitTarget, this))
1936 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1937 if (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ALLY
1938 || (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PARTY && caster->IsInPartyWith(unitTarget))
1939 || (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_RAID && caster->IsInRaidWith(unitTarget)))
1940 if (caster->_IsValidAssistTarget(unitTarget, this))
1941 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1942 if (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MINIPET)
1943 if (unitTarget->GetGUID() == caster->GetCritterGUID())
1944 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1945 if (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PASSENGER)
1946 if (unitTarget->IsOnVehicle(caster))
1947 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1948 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
1949 }
1950 }
1951 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
1952}

2046
2047AuraStateType SpellInfo::LoadAuraState() const
2048{
2049 // Seals
2050 if (GetSpellSpecific() == SPELL_SPECIFIC_SEAL)
2051 return AURA_STATE_JUDGEMENT;
2052
2053 // Conflagrate aura state on Immolate and Shadowflame
2054 if (SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_WARLOCK &&
2055 // Immolate
2056 ((SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 4) ||
2057 // Shadowflame
2058 (SpellFamilyFlags[2] & 2)))
2059 return AURA_STATE_CONFLAGRATE;
2060
2061 // Faerie Fire (druid versions)
2062 if (SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_DRUID && SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x400)
2063 return AURA_STATE_FAERIE_FIRE;
2064
2065 // Sting (hunter's pet ability)
2066 if (GetCategory() == 1133)
2067 return AURA_STATE_FAERIE_FIRE;
2068
2069 // Victorious
2070 if (SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_WARRIOR && SpellFamilyFlags[1] & 0x00040000)
2071 return AURA_STATE_WARRIOR_VICTORY_RUSH;
2072
2073 // Swiftmend state on Regrowth & Rejuvenation
2074 if (SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_DRUID && SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x50)
2075 return AURA_STATE_SWIFTMEND;
2076
2077 // Deadly poison aura state
2078 if (SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_ROGUE && SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x10000)
2079 return AURA_STATE_DEADLY_POISON;
2080
2081 // Enrage aura state
2082 if (Dispel == DISPEL_ENRAGE)
2083 return AURA_STATE_ENRAGE;
2084
2085 // Bleeding aura state
2086 if (GetAllEffectsMechanicMask() & 1 << MECHANIC_BLEED)
2087 return AURA_STATE_BLEEDING;
2088
2089 if (GetSchoolMask() & SPELL_SCHOOL_MASK_FROST)
2090 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2091 if (Effects[i].IsAura() && (Effects[i].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_STUN
2092 || Effects[i].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_ROOT))
2093 return AURA_STATE_FROZEN;
2094
2095 switch (Id)
2096 {
2097 case 71465: // Divine Surge
2098 case 50241: // Oculus, Drake spell Evasive Maneuvers
2099 return AURA_STATE_UNKNOWN22;
2100 case 9991: // Touch of Zanzil
2101 case 35331: // Black Blood
2102 case 9806: // Phantom Strike
2103 case 35325: // Glowing Blood
2104 case 16498: // Faerie Fire
2105 case 6950:
2106 case 20656:
2107 case 25602:
2108 case 32129:
2109 return AURA_STATE_FAERIE_FIRE;
2110 default:
2111 break;
2112 }
2113
2114 return AURA_STATE_NONE;
2115}

2119 return _spellSpecific;

2121
2122SpellSpecificType SpellInfo::LoadSpellSpecific() const
2123{
2124 switch (SpellFamilyName)
2125 {
2126 case SPELLFAMILY_GENERIC:
2127 {
2128 // Food / Drinks (mostly)
2129 if (AuraInterruptFlags & AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_NOT_SEATED)
2130 {
2131 bool food = false;
2132 bool drink = false;
2133 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2134 {
2135 if (!Effects[i].IsAura())
2136 continue;
2137 switch (Effects[i].ApplyAuraName)
2138 {
2139 // Food
2140 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_REGEN:
2141 case SPELL_AURA_OBS_MOD_HEALTH:
2142 food = true;
2143 break;
2144 // Drink
2145 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_POWER_REGEN:
2146 case SPELL_AURA_OBS_MOD_POWER:
2147 drink = true;
2148 break;
2149 default:
2150 break;
2151 }
2152 }
2153
2154 if (food && drink)
2155 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_FOOD_AND_DRINK;
2156 else if (food)
2157 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_FOOD;
2158 else if (drink)
2159 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_DRINK;
2160 }
2161 // scrolls effects
2162 else
2163 {
2164 SpellInfo const* firstRankSpellInfo = GetFirstRankSpell();
2165 switch (firstRankSpellInfo->Id)
2166 {
2167 case 8118: // Strength
2168 case 8099: // Stamina
2169 case 8112: // Spirit
2170 case 8096: // Intellect
2171 case 8115: // Agility
2172 case 8091: // Armor
2173 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_SCROLL;
2174 }
2175 }
2176 break;
2177 }
2178 case SPELLFAMILY_MAGE:
2179 {
2180 // family flags 18(Molten), 25(Frost/Ice), 28(Mage)
2181 if (SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x12040000)
2182 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_MAGE_ARMOR;
2183
2184 // Arcane brillance and Arcane intelect (normal check fails because of flags difference)
2185 if (SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x400)
2186 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_MAGE_ARCANE_BRILLANCE;
2187
2188 if ((SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x1000000) && Effects[0].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_CONFUSE)
2189 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_MAGE_POLYMORPH;
2190
2191 break;
2192 }
2193 case SPELLFAMILY_WARLOCK:
2194 {
2195 // only warlock curses have this
2196 if (Dispel == DISPEL_CURSE)
2197 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_CURSE;
2198
2199 // Warlock (Demon Armor | Demon Skin | Fel Armor)
2200 if (SpellFamilyFlags[1] & 0x20000020 || SpellFamilyFlags[2] & 0x00000010)
2201 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_WARLOCK_ARMOR;
2202
2203 //seed of corruption and corruption
2204 if (SpellFamilyFlags[1] & 0x10 || SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x2)
2205 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_WARLOCK_CORRUPTION;
2206 break;
2207 }
2208 case SPELLFAMILY_PRIEST:
2209 {
2210 // Divine Spirit and Prayer of Spirit
2211 if (SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x20)
2212 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_PRIEST_DIVINE_SPIRIT;
2213
2214 break;
2215 }
2216 case SPELLFAMILY_HUNTER:
2217 {
2218 // only hunter stings have this
2219 if (Dispel == DISPEL_POISON)
2220 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_STING;
2221
2222 // only hunter aspects have this (but not all aspects in hunter family)
2223 if (SpellFamilyFlags.HasFlag(0x00380000, 0x00440000, 0x00001010))
2224 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_ASPECT;
2225
2226 break;
2227 }
2228 case SPELLFAMILY_PALADIN:
2229 {
2230 // Collection of all the seal family flags. No other paladin spell has any of those.
2231 if (SpellFamilyFlags[1] & 0x26000C00
2232 || SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x0A000000)
2233 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_SEAL;
2234
2235 if (SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x00002190)
2236 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_HAND;
2237
2238 // Judgement of Wisdom, Judgement of Light, Judgement of Justice
2239 if (Id == 20184 || Id == 20185 || Id == 20186)
2240 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_JUDGEMENT;
2241
2242 // only paladin auras have this (for palaldin class family)
2243 if (SpellFamilyFlags[2] & 0x00000020)
2244 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_AURA;
2245
2246 // Illidari Council Paladin (Gathios the Shatterer)
2247 if (Id == 41459 || Id == 41469)
2248 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_SEAL;
2249
2250 break;
2251 }
2252 case SPELLFAMILY_SHAMAN:
2253 {
2254 // family flags 10 (Lightning), 42 (Earth), 37 (Water), proc shield from T2 8 pieces bonus
2255 if (SpellFamilyFlags[1] & 0x420
2256 || SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x00000400
2257 || Id == 23552)
2258 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_ELEMENTAL_SHIELD;
2259
2260 break;
2261 }
2262 case SPELLFAMILY_DEATHKNIGHT:
2263 if (Id == 48266 || Id == 48263 || Id == 48265)
2264 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_PRESENCE;
2265 break;
2266 }
2267
2268 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2269 {
2270 if (Effects[i].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA)
2271 {
2272 switch (Effects[i].ApplyAuraName)
2273 {
2274 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_CHARM:
2275 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_POSSESS_PET:
2276 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_POSSESS:
2277 case SPELL_AURA_AOE_CHARM:
2278 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_CHARM;
2279 case SPELL_AURA_TRACK_CREATURES:
2281 if (Id == 30645) // Gas Cloud Tracking
2282 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_NORMAL;
2283 [[fallthrough]]; // TODO: Not sure whether the fallthrough was a mistake (forgetting a break) or intended. This should be double-checked.
2284 case SPELL_AURA_TRACK_RESOURCES:
2285 case SPELL_AURA_TRACK_STEALTHED:
2286 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_TRACKER;
2287 }
2288 }
2289 }
2290
2291 return SPELL_SPECIFIC_NORMAL;
2292}

2348uint32 SpellInfo::GetMaxTicks() const
2349{
2350 int32 DotDuration = GetDuration();
2351 if (DotDuration == 0)
2352 return 1;
2353
2354 // 200% limit
2355 if (DotDuration > 30000)
2356 DotDuration = 30000;
2357
2358 for (uint8 x = 0; x < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; x++)
2359 {
2360 if (Effects[x].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA)
2361 switch (Effects[x].ApplyAuraName)

2363 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE:
2364 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_HEAL:
2365 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_LEECH:
2366 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL_FROM_CLIENT:
2367 if (Effects[x].Amplitude != 0)
2368 return DotDuration / Effects[x].Amplitude;
2369 break;
2370 }
2371 }
2372
2373 return 6;

2381int32 SpellInfo::CalcPowerCost(Unit const* caster, SpellSchoolMask schoolMask, Spell* spell) const
2382{
2383 // Spell drain all exist power on cast (Only paladin lay of Hands)
2384 if (AttributesEx & SPELL_ATTR1_USE_ALL_MANA)
2385 {
2386 // If power type - health drain all
2387 if (PowerType == POWER_HEALTH)
2388 return caster->GetHealth();
2389 // Else drain all power
2390 if (PowerType < MAX_POWERS)
2391 return caster->GetPower(Powers(PowerType));
2392 LOG_ERROR("spells", "SpellInfo::CalcPowerCost: Unknown power type '{}' in spell {}", PowerType, Id);
2393 return 0;
2394 }
2395
2396 // Base powerCost
2397 int32 powerCost = ManaCost;
2398 // PCT cost from total amount
2399 if (ManaCostPercentage)
2400 {
2401 switch (PowerType)
2402 {
2403 // health as power used
2404 case POWER_HEALTH:
2405 powerCost += int32(CalculatePct(caster->GetCreateHealth(), ManaCostPercentage));
2406 break;
2407 case POWER_MANA:
2408 powerCost += int32(CalculatePct(caster->GetCreateMana(), ManaCostPercentage));
2409 break;
2410 case POWER_RAGE:
2411 case POWER_FOCUS:
2412 case POWER_ENERGY:
2413 case POWER_HAPPINESS:
2414 powerCost += int32(CalculatePct(caster->GetMaxPower(Powers(PowerType)), ManaCostPercentage));
2415 break;
2416 case POWER_RUNE:
2417 case POWER_RUNIC_POWER:
2418 LOG_DEBUG("spells.aura", "CalculateManaCost: Not implemented yet!");
2419 break;
2420 default:
2421 LOG_ERROR("spells", "CalculateManaCost: Unknown power type '{}' in spell {}", PowerType, Id);
2422 return 0;
2423 }
2424 }
2425 SpellSchools school = GetFirstSchoolInMask(schoolMask);
2426 // Flat mod from caster auras by spell school
2427 powerCost += caster->GetInt32Value(static_cast<uint16>(UNIT_FIELD_POWER_COST_MODIFIER) + school);
2428
2429 // Shiv - costs 20 + weaponSpeed*10 energy (apply only to non-triggered spell with energy cost)
2430 if (AttributesEx4 & SPELL_ATTR4_WEAPON_SPEED_COST_SCALING)
2431 {
2432 uint32 speed = 0;
2433 if (SpellShapeshiftEntry const* ss = sSpellShapeshiftStore.LookupEntry(caster->GetShapeshiftForm()))
2434 speed = ss->attackSpeed;
2435 else
2436 {
2437 WeaponAttackType slot = BASE_ATTACK;
2438 if (AttributesEx3 & SPELL_ATTR3_REQUIRES_OFF_HAND_WEAPON)
2439 slot = OFF_ATTACK;
2440
2441 speed = caster->GetAttackTime(slot);
2442 }
2443
2444 powerCost += speed / 100;
2445 }
2446
2447 // Apply cost mod by spell
2448 if (Player* modOwner = caster->GetSpellModOwner())
2449 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(Id, SPELLMOD_COST, powerCost, spell);
2450
2451 if (!caster->IsControlledByPlayer())
2452 {
2453 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_SCALES_WITH_CREATURE_LEVEL))
2454 {
2455 GtNPCManaCostScalerEntry const* spellScaler = sGtNPCManaCostScalerStore.LookupEntry(SpellLevel - 1);
2456 GtNPCManaCostScalerEntry const* casterScaler = sGtNPCManaCostScalerStore.LookupEntry(caster->getLevel() - 1);
2457 if (spellScaler && casterScaler)
2458 powerCost *= casterScaler->ratio / spellScaler->ratio;
2459 }
2460 }
2461
2462 // PCT mod from user auras by school
2463 powerCost = int32(powerCost * (1.0f + caster->GetFloatValue(static_cast<uint16>(UNIT_FIELD_POWER_COST_MULTIPLIER) + school)));
2464 if (powerCost < 0)
2465 powerCost = 0;
2466 return powerCost;
2467}

2506SpellInfo const* SpellInfo::GetAuraRankForLevel(uint8 level) const
2507{
2508 // ignore passive spells
2509 //if (IsPassive())
2510 // return this;
2511
2512 bool needRankSelection = false;
2513 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2514 {
2515 if (IsPositiveEffect(i) &&
2516 (Effects[i].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA ||
2517 Effects[i].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AREA_AURA_PARTY ||
2518 Effects[i].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AREA_AURA_RAID))
2519 {
2520 needRankSelection = true;
2521 break;
2522 }
2523 }
2524
2525 // not required
2526 if (!needRankSelection)
2527 return this;
2528
2529 SpellInfo const* nextSpellInfo = nullptr;
2530
2531 sScriptMgr->OnBeforeAuraRankForLevel(this, nextSpellInfo, level);
2532
2533 if (nextSpellInfo != nullptr)
2534 return nextSpellInfo;
2535
2536 for (nextSpellInfo = this; nextSpellInfo != nullptr; nextSpellInfo = nextSpellInfo->GetPrevRankSpell())
2537 {
2538 // if found appropriate level
2539 if (uint32(level + 10) >= nextSpellInfo->SpellLevel)
2540 return nextSpellInfo;
2541
2542 // one rank less then
2543 }
2544
2545 // not found
2546 return nullptr;
2547}

2572void SpellInfo::_InitializeExplicitTargetMask()
2573{
2574 bool srcSet = false;
2575 bool dstSet = false;
2576 uint32 targetMask = Targets;
2577 // prepare target mask using effect target entries
2578 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2579 {
2580 if (!Effects[i].IsEffect())
2581 continue;
2582 targetMask |= Effects[i].TargetA.GetExplicitTargetMask(srcSet, dstSet);
2583 targetMask |= Effects[i].TargetB.GetExplicitTargetMask(srcSet, dstSet);
2584
2585 // add explicit target flags based on spell effects which have EFFECT_IMPLICIT_TARGET_EXPLICIT and no valid target provided
2586 if (Effects[i].GetImplicitTargetType() != EFFECT_IMPLICIT_TARGET_EXPLICIT)
2587 continue;
2588
2589 // extend explicit target mask only if valid targets for effect could not be provided by target types
2590 uint32 effectTargetMask = Effects[i].GetMissingTargetMask(srcSet, dstSet, targetMask);
2591
2592 // don't add explicit object/dest flags when spell has no max range
2593 if (GetMaxRange(true) == 0.0f && GetMaxRange(false) == 0.0f)
2594 effectTargetMask &= ~(TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION);
2595 targetMask |= effectTargetMask;
2596 }
2597 ExplicitTargetMask = targetMask;
2598}

2600bool SpellInfo::_IsPositiveEffect(uint8 effIndex, bool deep) const
2601{
2602 // not found a single positive spell with this attribute
2603 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_AURA_IS_DEBUFF))
2604 return false;
2605
2606 switch (Mechanic)
2607 {
2608 case MECHANIC_IMMUNE_SHIELD:
2609 return true;
2610 default:
2611 break;
2612 }
2613
2614 // Special case: effects which determine positivity of whole spell
2615 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2616 {
2617 if (Effects[i].IsAura() && Effects[i].ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_STEALTH)
2618 return true;
2619 }
2620
2621 switch (Effects[effIndex].Effect)
2622 {
2623 case SPELL_EFFECT_DUMMY:
2624 // some explicitly required dummy effect sets
2625 switch (Id)
2626 {
2627 case 28441:
2628 return false; // AB Effect 000
2629 default:
2630 break;
2631 }
2632 break;
2633 // always positive effects (check before target checks that provided non-positive result in some case for positive effects)
2634 case SPELL_EFFECT_HEAL:
2635 case SPELL_EFFECT_LEARN_SPELL:
2636 case SPELL_EFFECT_SKILL_STEP:
2637 case SPELL_EFFECT_HEAL_PCT:
2638 case SPELL_EFFECT_ENERGIZE_PCT:
2639 return true;
2640 case SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AREA_AURA_ENEMY:
2641 return false;
2642
2643 case SPELL_EFFECT_GAMEOBJECT_DAMAGE:
2644 return false;
2645
2646 case SPELL_EFFECT_SCHOOL_DAMAGE:
2647 {
2648 bool only = true;
2649 for (int i = EFFECT_0; i <= EFFECT_2; ++i)
2650 {
2651 if (Effects[effIndex].Effect > 0 && Effects[effIndex].Effect != SPELL_EFFECT_SCHOOL_DAMAGE)
2652 only = false;
2653 if (Effects[effIndex].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_GAMEOBJECT_DAMAGE)
2654 return false;
2655 }
2656 // effects with school damage only cannot be positive...
2657 if (only)
2658 return false;
2659 break;
2660 }
2661 case SPELL_EFFECT_KNOCK_BACK:
2662 case SPELL_EFFECT_KNOCK_BACK_DEST:
2663 {
2664 for (int i = EFFECT_0; i <= EFFECT_2; ++i)
2665 if (Effects[effIndex].Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_GAMEOBJECT_DAMAGE)
2666 return false;
2667 break;
2668 }
2669
2670 // non-positive aura use
2671 case SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA:
2672 case SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AREA_AURA_FRIEND:
2673 {
2674 switch (Effects[effIndex].ApplyAuraName)
2675 {
2676 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_DONE: // dependent from bas point sign (negative -> negative)
2677 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_STAT:
2678 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_SKILL:
2679 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DODGE_PERCENT:
2680 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_HEALING_PCT:
2681 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_HEALING_DONE:
2682 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_PERCENT_DONE:
2683 if (Effects[effIndex].CalcValue() < 0)
2684 return false;
2685 break;
2686 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DAMAGE_TAKEN: // dependent from bas point sign (positive -> negative)
2687 if (Effects[effIndex].CalcValue() > 0)
2688 return false;
2689 break;
2690 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_CRIT_PCT:
2691 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_SPELL_CRIT_CHANCE:
2692 if (Effects[effIndex].CalcValue() > 0)
2693 return true; // some expected positive spells have SPELL_ATTR1_NEGATIVE
2694 break;
2695 case SPELL_AURA_ADD_TARGET_TRIGGER:
2696 return true;
2697 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL_WITH_VALUE:
2698 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL_FROM_CLIENT:
2699 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_TRIGGER_SPELL:
2700 if (!deep)
2701 {
2702 if (SpellInfo const* spellTriggeredProto = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(Effects[effIndex].TriggerSpell))
2703 {
2704 // negative targets of main spell return early
2705 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2706 {
2707 if (!spellTriggeredProto->Effects[i].Effect)
2708 continue;
2709 // if non-positive trigger cast targeted to positive target this main cast is non-positive
2710 // this will place this spell auras as debuffs
2711 if (_IsPositiveTarget(spellTriggeredProto->Effects[i].TargetA.GetTarget(), spellTriggeredProto->Effects[i].TargetB.GetTarget()) && !spellTriggeredProto->_IsPositiveEffect(i, true))
2712 return false;
2713 }
2714 }
2715 }
2716 case SPELL_AURA_PROC_TRIGGER_SPELL:
2717 // many positive auras have negative triggered spells at damage for example and this not make it negative (it can be canceled for example)
2718 break;
2719 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_STUN: //have positive and negative spells, we can't sort its correctly at this moment.
2720 if (effIndex == 0 && Effects[1].Effect == 0 && Effects[2].Effect == 0)
2721 return false; // but all single stun aura spells is negative
2722 break;
2723 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_PACIFY_SILENCE:
2724 if (Id == 24740) // Wisp Costume
2725 return true;
2726 return false;
2727 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_ROOT:
2728 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_SILENCE:
2729 case SPELL_AURA_GHOST:
2730 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_LEECH:
2731 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_STALKED:
2732 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE_PERCENT:
2733 case SPELL_AURA_PREVENT_RESURRECTION:
2734 return false;
2735 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_DAMAGE: // used in positive spells also.
2736 // part of negative spell if casted at self (prevent cancel)
2737 if (Effects[effIndex].TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_CASTER)
2738 return false;
2739 break;
2740 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_DECREASE_SPEED: // used in positive spells also
2741 // part of positive spell if casted at self
2742 if (Effects[effIndex].TargetA.GetTarget() != TARGET_UNIT_CASTER)
2743 return false;
2744 // but not this if this first effect (didn't find better check)
2745 if (HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_AURA_IS_DEBUFF) && effIndex == 0)
2746 return false;
2747 break;
2748 case SPELL_AURA_MECHANIC_IMMUNITY:
2749 {
2750 // non-positive immunities
2751 switch (Effects[effIndex].MiscValue)
2752 {
2753 case MECHANIC_BANDAGE:
2754 case MECHANIC_SHIELD:
2755 case MECHANIC_MOUNT:
2756 case MECHANIC_INVULNERABILITY:
2757 return false;
2758 default:
2759 break;
2760 }
2761 break;
2762 }
2763 case SPELL_AURA_ADD_FLAT_MODIFIER: // mods
2764 case SPELL_AURA_ADD_PCT_MODIFIER:
2765 {
2766 // non-positive mods
2767 switch (Effects[effIndex].MiscValue)
2768 {
2769 case SPELLMOD_COST: // dependent from bas point sign (negative -> positive)
2770 if (Effects[effIndex].CalcValue() > 0)
2771 {
2772 if (!deep)
2773 {
2774 bool negative = true;
2775 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
2776 {
2777 if (i != effIndex)
2778 if (_IsPositiveEffect(i, true))
2779 {
2780 negative = false;
2781 break;
2782 }
2783 }
2784 if (negative)
2785 return false;
2786 }
2787 }
2788 break;
2789 default:
2790 break;
2791 }
2792 break;
2793 }
2794 default:
2795 break;
2796 }
2797 break;
2798 }
2799 default:
2800 break;
2801 }
2802
2803 // non-positive targets
2804 if (!_IsPositiveTarget(Effects[effIndex].TargetA.GetTarget(), Effects[effIndex].TargetB.GetTarget()))
2805 return false;
2806
2807 // negative spell if triggered spell is negative
2808 if (!deep && !Effects[effIndex].ApplyAuraName && Effects[effIndex].TriggerSpell)
2809 {
2810 if (SpellInfo const* spellTriggeredProto = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(Effects[effIndex].TriggerSpell))
2811 if (!spellTriggeredProto->_IsPositiveSpell())
2812 return false;
2813 }
2814
2815 // ok, positive
2816 return true;
2817}

2869bool SpellInfo::CheckElixirStacking(Unit const* caster) const
2870{

2872 {
2873 return true;
2874 }
2875
2876 // xinef: check spell group
2877 uint32 groupId = sSpellMgr->GetSpellGroup(Id);

2892 for (Unit::AuraApplicationMap::const_iterator itr = Auras.begin(); itr != Auras.end(); ++itr)
2893 {
2894 // xinef: aura is not groupped or in different group
2895 uint32 auraGroup = sSpellMgr->GetSpellGroup(itr->first);
2896 if (auraGroup != groupId)
2897 {
2898 continue;
2899 }
2900
2901 // Cannot apply guardian/battle elixir if flask is present
2902 if (sFlag == SPELL_GROUP_SPECIAL_FLAG_ELIXIR_BATTLE || sFlag == SPELL_GROUP_SPECIAL_FLAG_ELIXIR_GUARDIAN)

2905 if ((sAuraFlag & SPELL_GROUP_SPECIAL_FLAG_FLASK) == SPELL_GROUP_SPECIAL_FLAG_FLASK)
